Deputy Court Clerk kmh.
Statements made as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 1 -   
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 25 YEARS, consecutive to and other sentence, with credit for 125 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 10 YEARS.  
Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Earned Release Program. The defendant is not appropriate for the Risk Reduction program.
Extradition costs, court costs and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Complete 500 hours of community service (adults only  not with anyone under 16 years or vulnerable adult); 
2) No further violations of the law rising to the level of probable cause; 
3) Mental health evaluation and take all prescribed medication; 
4) AODA assessment and comply with any treatment;
5) No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia; 
6) Absolute sobriety with random urine screens; 
7) Attend treatment and counseling programs as determined by agent; 
8) No contact with the victims;
9) No contact with children under the age of 16 (court will allow supervised contact with defendant's own children once the defendant is released from custody); 
10) Register and comply with the sex offender registry;
11) Obtain/comply with sex offender treatment (while in custody and on extended supervision); 
13) Seek/maintain employment;
14) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
15) Pay all supervision fees;
16) Restitution set at ZERO;
17) Pay Extradition cost of $2640.00 to State of Wisconsin; 
18) Pay applicable costs, surcharges, victim/witness surcharge and assessments; any balance remaining unpaid is to be converted to a civil judgment against the defendant. 
Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting and Child sex offender working with children.
Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
